Riigikogu.label: Riigikogu
Riigikogu.description: The Riigikogu is the unicameral parliament of Estonia. All important state-related questions pass through the Riigikogu. Wikipedia

Tripura Tribal Areas Autonomous District.label: Tripura Tribal Areas Autonomous District Council
Tripura Tribal Areas Autonomous District.description: The Tripura Tribal Areas Autonomous District Council is an independent council administering the tribal areas of the state of Tripura, India. Its council and assembly are situated in Khumulwng, a town 26 km away from Agartala, the state capital. Wikipedia

Scottish Parliament.label: Scottish Parliament
Scottish Parliament.description: The Scottish Parliament is the devolved national, unicameral legislature of Scotland, located in the Holyrood area of the capital, Edinburgh. Wikipedia

Sutton London Borough Council.label: London Borough of Sutton
Sutton London Borough Council.description: The London Borough of Sutton is a London borough in South London, England and forms part of Outer London. It covers an area of 43 km² and is the 80th largest local authority in England by population. It is one of the southernmost boroughs of London. Wikipedia
University: Sutton College of Learning for Adults

West Sussex County Council.label: West Sussex County Council
West Sussex County Council.description: West Sussex County Council is the authority that governs the non-metropolitan county of West Sussex. The county also contains 7 district and borough councils, and 159 town, parish and neighbourhood councils. Wikipedia

Suffolk County Council.label: Suffolk County Council
Suffolk County Council.description: Suffolk County Council is the administrative authority for the county of Suffolk, England. It is run by 75 elected county councillors representing 63 divisions. It is a member of the East of England Local Government Association. Wikipedia

House of Commons of England.label: House of Commons of England
House of Commons of England.description: The House of Commons of England was the lower house of the Parliament of England from its development in the 14th century to the union of England and Scotland in 1707, when it was replaced by the House of Commons of Great Britain. Wikipedia

Cotswold District Council.label: Cotswold District
Cotswold District Council.description: Cotswold is a local government district in Gloucestershire in England. It is named after the wider Cotswolds region. Its main town is Cirencester. Wikipedia

Kensington and Chelsea London Borough Co.label: Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea
Kensington and Chelsea London Borough Co.description: The Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea is a west London borough of Royal borough status. It is an urban area, one of the most densely populated in the United Kingdom. Wikipedia

Legislative Assembly of Nunavut.label: Legislative Assembly of Nunavut
Legislative Assembly of Nunavut.description: The Legislative Assembly of Nunavut, Canada, is located in Iqaluit, and is the territory's parliament. Wikipedia
